ℹ️Printing Info: Items are produced using Direct To Garment Printing -DTG, which sprays the ink directly on to the fabric. Because the fabric absorbs the ink, the colors may not appear as vivid as the mocked up photos. This process is different than screen or vinyl printing, and because of this process the items graphic is more durable and longer lasting. We do our best to provide the best possible depiction that we can. Also, in some cases we do provide fabric colors that are similar to the colors in the print because we like some shirts to have less contrast and to provide a kind of camouflaged or subtle effect (i.e., black print on dark grey fabric, you get the idea). If you choose one of the items with this effect, please be aware that the graphics will be less visible. Feel free to reach out to me with questions. I have ordered many samples for myself, and have personally viewed items purchased by friends and can honestly say that the graphics have turned out as expected.

🖼️Artwork & Production:
All of my products are Made-To-Order using print-on-demand providers: I use production partners across the U.S., Canada, and in some cases a country as close to the destination country as possible to print or embroider my one-of-a-kind designs onto the products I sell. These partners then ship the item directly to you for me which results in a faster delivery to my awesome customers.😀

My original artwork and one-of-a-kind designs are created using a combination of my own ideas and research; artwork, clip art, edited AI generated graphics, and unique fonts.
